hoot Power Lift Recliner Chairs.";i:1;s:91:"The first step of troubleshooting a power lift recliner is to check you have plugged it in.";i:2;s:86:"Make sure the socket has power by plugging in something else and seeing if that works.";i:3;s:58:"From there follow the cables that connect to the recliner.";i:4;s:34:"Are any of them damaged or broken.";i:5;s:147:"Check the chairs transformer motor and relay box under the chair as a malfunction in any of these could cause the chair to stop working completely.";i:6;s:95:"The hand control used by the operator to change the chairs position may also be malfunctioning.";i:7;s:42:"Test the chairs wood frame bolts and lift.";i:8;s:43:"How to Troubleshooting Repair a Lift Chair.";i:9;s:110:"In this video I will demonstrate how to troubleshoot and repair a malfunctioning lift chair by performing som.";i:10;s:78:"Most lift chair failures are electrical in nature so check these things first.";i:11;s:98:"Make sure the chair is securely plugged in to the wall outlet and make sure the outlet is working.";i:12;s:78:"Check this by plugging something elsesmall lamp like a in to that same outlet.";i:13;s:56:"Sometimes wall switches control electrical wall outlets.";i:14;s:20:"Has the wall switch.";i:15;s:40:"Lift Chair Problems and Possible Causes.";i:16;s:289:"Lift Chair has stopped working Transformer Motor Hand control Motor relay box Control box Lift Chair is squeaking Scissors Wood frame is loose Bolts are too tight or too loose Lift frame is rubbing on wood frame Lift Chair is making popping noise Scissors Wood frame T-bracket is catching.";i:17;s:128:"If your stair lift was left unplugged for a very long time the batteries might have drained and your stair chair lift wont move.";i:18;s:109:"Plugging in the battery charger to the wall outlet may or may not recharge the batteriesbut its worth a shot.";i:19;s:122:"Yes theres a reset button on most remote controls in power recliners that you can use to reset the chair and make it work.";i:20;s:101:"This is mostly useful when the motor shuts down because there was a power surge or something similar.";i:21;s:178:"If everything above is checked and the sofa still isnt working properly you may need to replace the actuator and possibly the armrest with the controls for that side of the sofa.";i:22;s:85:"The metal frame lift or the scissor mechanism could be broken and need a replacement.";i:23;s:98:"Each sensor will stop the lift in a specific direction and are referred to as directional sensors.";i:24;s:76:"This will allow a chair to move in the opposite direction of an obstruction.";i:25;s:145:"For example if the chair was traveling down the stairs and the footrest hit an obstruction you would be able to move the lift back up the stairs.";i:26;s:46:"What if my lift chair does not operate at all.";i:27;s:83:"Ensure the external transformer is plugged into a properly wired electrical outlet.";i:28;s:105:"Check the circuit breaker box connected to the electrical outlet to ensure the outlet is receiving power.";i:29;s:81:"Ensure the low voltage connection cable is plugged into the external transformer.";i:30;s:140:"Here are some common problems to watch out for and solutions from the experts lift manufacturers and school bus mechanics around the nation.";i:31;s:105:"Outboard stop flaps Problems with wheelchair lifts are often caused by drivers operating them improperly.";i:32;s:57:"One of the more prominent issues is damage to stop flaps.";i:33;s:56:"Many chairs have been rated for a maximum of 225 pounds.";i:34;s:65:"If you weigh more than that ask about chairs with higher ratings.";i:35;s:50:"You may have to consider special ordering a chair.";i:36;s:24:"Age of the gas cylinder.";i:37;s:62:"Some gas cylinders naturally stop working correctly over time.";i:38;s:81:"You may have a chair for more than 10 years and suddenly the gas cylinder begins.";i:39;s:51:"The lift runs fine sometimes but can stop randomly.";i:40;s:87:"This could be a variety of things including an electrical short or a safety adjustment.";i:41;s:124:"Unusual operation Lift jumps shutters or hesitates on the track with grinding noise the likely cause is a gearbox going bad.";i:42;s:94:"A Lift Chair is a piece of medical equipment that looks similar to a standard reclining chair.";i:43;s:81:"It can be used in an upright position or reclined with just the push of a button.";i:44;s:165:"The difference is that the Lift Chair contains a powerful lifting system which can be triggered to tilt the base and back of the chair forward assisting the user in.";i:45;s:32:"Stairlift Is Constantly Beeping.";i:46;s:131:"If your stair lift is beeping all the time then its quite likely that its either not on a charge point or the charger is unplugged.";i:47;s:74:"Failing this then its most likely a faulty charger that needs replacement.";i:48;s:54:"All stair lift chairs have a standard swivel position.";i:49;s:109:"If the seat is swiveled towards the landing the chair wont work and will keep alerting you about the problem.";i:50;s:107:"Swivel the chair back to its riding position after each use and the mechanism will lock it back into place.";i:51;s:19:"If the position is.";i:52;s:76:"Air flow issues are compounded the longer one sits in a lift recliner chair.";i:53;s:135:"If your lifestyle suggests that you will be sitting in your recliner lift chair for long periods at a time you should go with a fabric.";i:54;s:48:"Vinyl and leather are poor choices in this case.";i:55;s:98:"Fold the chair footrest and armrests up and then put everything back down again just to make sure.";i:56;s:70:"Is the swivel seat locked firmly into place and facing straight ahead.";i:57;s:74:"Wiggle the stairlift from side to side until you hear it click into place.";i:58;s:91:"Have any and all obstructions been removed from near the Bruno stairlift carriage and rail.";i:59;s:101:"Many office chairs have a pneumatic cylinder that enables the user to adjust the height of the chair.";i:60;s:127:"Occasionally the cylinder may leak causing the pneumatics to fail and allowing your chair to sink slowly as the day progresses.";i:61;s:67:"This can be incredibly frustrating but is quite easy to fix -- and.";i:62;s:42:"Your lift chair is only reclining partway.";i:63;s:65:"When you need lift chair repair We are your lift chair repairman.";i:64;s:28:"We work on all major brands.";i:65;s:144:"Golden Technologies Pride Mobility Pride Lift Regis Coaster Yandel Berkline Infinite Canmov AmeriGlide Medline American Quality Health and more.";i:66;s:84:"And after only a few years or less of using the chair it just seems to stop working.";i:67;s:105:"Even though it still looks almost brand new and in good shape it sinks and the office chair wont stay up.";i:68;s:96:"Whether youve spent 100 or 1500 on a desk chair no one should have to deal with an office chair.";}}